<item>
            <title>[LU-10345] allow specifying file layout by FID and filename extension</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10345</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It would be useful for users to be able to specify the file layout to use based on the filename extension.  For example, choose a widely-striped layout for &lt;tt&gt;.mpg&lt;/tt&gt; movies, choose a single-striped layout for &lt;tt&gt;.mp3&lt;/tt&gt; audio files, and choose no-compression options for files with &lt;tt&gt;.gz&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;.bz2&lt;/tt&gt; extensions. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the first implementation, we might consider storing a table on the MDS of extension-&amp;gt;FID mappings, where the referenced FID is used as the template for new files.  An improvement on this would allow users to specify such a table on a parent directory, so they can create mappings without the input of the sysadmin.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
